<!DOCTYPE rkplugin>
<document>
    <code file="two_independent_samples_t_test.js" />
    <help file="two_independent_samples_t_test.rkh" />
    
    <logic>
        <connect governor="factor.available" client="levels.variable" />
        <connect governor="variable.available" client="filter_embed.variable" />
    </logic>
    
    <dialog label="t-tesf for comparing the means of two independent populations">
        <tabbook>
            <tab id="tab_variables" label="Variables">
                <row id="row_vars">
                    <varselector id="selector" label="Select variables" />
                    <column>
                        <varslot id="variable" label="Compare means of" source="selector" types="number" required="true" />
                        <varslot id="factor" label="According to" source="selector" types="factor" required="true" />
                        <frame id="levels_frame" label="Populations to compare">
                            <row>
                                <column>
                                    <text>Levels</text>
                                    <embed id="levels" component="rkward::level_select" />
                                </column>
                                <column>
                                    <valueslot id="population1" label="Compare population" source="levels.selector" />
                                    <valueslot id="population2" label="With population" source="levels.selector" />
                                </column>
                            </row>
                        </frame>
                        <embed id="filter_embed" component="rkTeaching::filter_embed" />
                        <stretch />
                    </column>
                </row>
            </tab>
            <tab id="tab_settings" label="Test options">
                <row>
                    <column>
                        <radio id="hypothesis" label="Alternative hypothesis">
                            <option value="two.sided" label="Two-sided (&#8800;)" />
                            <option value="greater" label="Greater (&gt;)" />
                            <option value="less" label="Less (&lt;)" />
                        </radio>
                        <frame id="confint_frame" label="Confidence interval for the difference of means" checkable="true" checked="true" value="1">
                            <spinbox id="conflevel" label="Confidence level" type="real" min="0" max="0.99" initial="0.95" />
                        </frame>
                        <stretch />
                    </column>
                </row>
            </tab>
        </tabbook>
    </dialog>
    
    <wizard label="t-tesf for comparing the means of two independent populations wizard">
        <page>
            <text>
                <p>
                    This procedure does the Student t-test for detecting a significant difference between the means of two  independent populations and estimating the difference with a confidence interval.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The dependent variable must be numeric and the independent variable must be a factor.
                </p>
            </text>
        </page>
        <page>
            <text>
                <p>
                    Insert the numeric variable for which to compare the means in the field <b>Compare</b>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    After, insert the factor in the field <b>According to</b>.
                </p>
                <p>Next, select the category of the factor for the first population in the field <b>Compare population</b> and the category for the second population in the field <b>With population</b>.</p>
            </text>
            <copy id="row_vars" />
            <stretch />
        </page>
        <page>
            <text>
                <p>Select the type of alternative hypothesis to test:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Check two-sided you have no assumption about what mean is greater.</li>
                    <li>Check greater if you assume that the mean of the first population is greater than the mean of the second population.</li>
                    <li>Check less if you assume that the mean of the first population is less than the mean of the second population.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>The one-sided hypothesis tends to increase the power of the test.</p>
            </text>
            <copy id="hypothesis" />
            <stretch />
        </page>
        <page>
            <text>
                <p>If you wants a confidence interval to estimate the difference between the means of the populations check the box and enter the desired confidence level (a 95% of confidence correspond to a 5% of significance).</p>
            </text>
            <copy id="confint_frame" />
            <stretch />
        </page>
    </wizard>
</document>
